dslRuleAfterChange:
A hypothetical DSL construct for inserting a guard could be:

<insertGuardBeforeStatement>
  $cmd.getName()
  :: ! $cmd.isHandled() || ! $cmd.isEnabled()
  =>
  if (! $cmd.isHandled() || ! $cmd.isEnabled()) {
      return;
  }
</insertGuardBeforeStatement>
;;

This would require significant DSL extensions to handle multi-statement insertions and control flow manipulation.
